node.text:
If you truly want to be great, spend every waking hour helping others to be great first.🔥🤔💯😏

So many people want to be Kings and Queens yet they do not know how to be Servants. And they will fail because they desire power but not responsibility. Even worse, they want power for themselves and not for the good of others. This attitude is not only arrogant but will surely lead to destruction.

node.text:
🏆You spend money endlessly to fake impress others for likes on social media knowing you are struggling.🤔👀😒🤦🏾‍♂️

Why is it when the new iPhone drop you have $300, $400, $500, $600 ready..
When the new Jordans drop you are standing in line for hours and ready to drop $200, $300, $400.
When you need some hair you’re ready to drop $200, $300, $400 on the best brazilian bundles.
When you want to buy Red Bottoms or a Gucci Bag money is no object.
On the weekend you go out and spend $200, $300, $400, $500 in the club to impress people with not a care in the world.

But when it's time to invest in yourselves to make moves to better your situation it's always "I don't have any money", "I'm broke right now", "I'm low on cash", "waiting on next month" etc etc etc excuse after excuse. You are lying to yourself.  You are not broke, you are just scared because you think you will fail. You have no faith in yourself to WIN. You have it for material items all the time but don't value yourself to invest in yourself. Think about that! You don't even see the value in yourself to spend on YOU! That mindset has to change. I'm telling you if you focus on your dreams and invest in yourself to become successful you can have whatever you want in life. Just create the vision that makes you want to jump out the bed in the morning and I promise you will succeed.
